The '''Bright Lands''' was the name given to the side of [[Ryloth/Legends|Ryloth]] that was baked in constant [[Star/Legends|sunlight]] during the daytime. Traditionally, [[Twi'lek/Legends|Twi'lek]] clan leaders were sent here to die if one of their fellow clan leaders had died, either from natural causes or in some cases, assassination. This tradition was instrumental in the changing of hands within the planetary government. In extreme cases, criminals were also exiled to the Bright Lands as a form of capital punishment.

According to tradition, [[Inun (mythology)|Inun]] was a blind youth famous for crossing the Bright Lands.<ref name="GCG">''[[Galactic Campaign Guide]]''</ref> Also, in [[28 BBY/Legends|28 BBY]] the [[Twi'lek/Legends|Twi'lek]] [[Ro Fenn]] was sent into the Bright Lands when his fellow council member [[Pol Secura]] was accidentally killed at the hands of his niece [[Aayla Secura/Legends|Aayla Secura]].

